task.summary: Reduce time between long flushed in FlushDataInterfacesThread
Make sure RemoteDatabaseInterfaceFactory can be wired in spring
Updated benchmarks, added description and images of results
Removed reference to rocksDB* from test with java objects
Fixed bug in DataInterfaceFactory that broke writing bloom filter when closing BloomFilterDataInterface
Fixed bug when iterating over files, added locking of directory, close data interface on error
Make sure we also release write lock on error
fix bug: use correct port in RemoteFile.java
Added class to inspect a binary file written by FileDataInterface
Better lifecycle management of data interfaces
Don't use DatabaseServerDataInterfaceFactory, don't keep track of number of reads and writes
Make sure the bloomfilter is also flushed, don't use WebContainerConfiguration and fixed some issues in the remote file server
Various speed improvements with multi-threaded write buffer
Moved to java 1.8, various speed improvements
Updated documentation with new benchmark results
Made LongBloomFilterWithCheckSum byte array serializable, various speed improvements for large datasets
In CachedDataInterface, only flush write cache to free memory
No need to specify cached type in ExampleUsage.java
Renamed SimpleString and ExtendedString to BowString and BowStringImpl
Neither use a bloom filter in IndexedDataInterface
Updated documentation with latest performance figures
Fixed bug in RemoteDataInterface.java that for iterators that are not fully iterated
Modified application context factories to style of bow-utils v1.1.10, fixed TestRemoteFileService.java
Release v1.1.12. Improved auto-wiring and support for streams
